格。 “如果可用性可以随着基础设施的发展而提高，我们就可以减少电池的数量，”他说，并指出需要扩大充电设施并提供政府支持。 </p><figure class="center_c1symtaw figure_f1xkd112 figure_fv30jf" data-image-viewer-target="true" data-src-for-image-viewer="https://article-image-ix.nikkei.com/https%3A%2F%2Fimgix-proxy.n8s.jp%2FDSXZQO3368222019052023000000-1.jpg?ixlib=js-3.8.0&amp;w=680&amp;h=510&amp;auto=format%2Ccompress&amp;fit=crop&amp;bg=FFFFFF&amp;s=e1230cd4ec7ae79dafa9e70badb3eee4"><div class="pictureWrapper_p13ffdka" style="max-width:430px"><div style="max-width:430px"><picture class="picture_p169s49k" style="padding-bottom:75.11627906976744%;width:430px"><source srcset="https://article-image-ix.nikkei.com/https%3A%2F%2Fimgix-proxy.n8s.jp%2FDSXZQO3368222019052023000000-1.jpg?ixlib=js-3.8.0&amp;w=430&amp;h=323&amp;auto=format%2Ccompress&amp;fit=crop&amp;bg=FFFFFF&amp;s=25830df0bf71b93df118bae24e465553" media="(min-width: 1232px)"><source srcset="https://article-image-ix.nikkei.com/https%3A%2F%2Fimgix-proxy.n8s.jp%2FDSXZQO3368222019052023000000-1.jpg?ixlib=js-3.8.0&amp;w=430&amp;h=323&amp;auto=format%2Ccompress&amp;fit=crop&amp;bg=FFFFFF&amp;s=25830df0bf71b93df118bae24e465553" media="(min-width: 992px)"><source srcset="https://article-image-ix.nikkei.com/https%3A%2F%2Fimgix-proxy.n8s.jp%2FDSXZQO3368222019052023000000-1.jpg?ixlib=js-3.8.0&amp;w=430&amp;h=323&amp;auto=format%2Ccompress&amp;fit=crop&amp;bg=FFFFFF&amp;s=25830df0bf71b93df118bae24e465553" media="(min-width: 752px)"><source srcset="https://article-image-ix.nikkei.com/https%3A%2F%2Fimgix-proxy.n8s.jp%2FDSXZQO3368222019052023000000-1.jpg?ixlib=js-3.8.0&amp;w=430&amp;h=323&amp;auto=format%2Ccompress&amp;fit=crop&amp;bg=FFFFFF&amp;s=25830df0bf71b93df118bae24e465553" media="(min-width: 316px)"><source srcset="https://article-image-ix.nikkei.com/https%3A%2F%2Fimgix-proxy.n8s.jp%2FDSXZQO3368222019052023000000-1.jpg?ixlib=js-3.8.0&amp;w=430&amp;h=323&amp;auto=format%2Ccompress&amp;fit=crop&amp;bg=FFFFFF&amp;s=25830df0bf71b93df118bae24e465553" media="(min-width: 0px)"><img loading